org.freedesktop.wayland.util

Class ObjectCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.freedesktop.wayland.util.ObjectCache

  • public class ObjectCache
extends java.lang.Object
    A cache for POJOs with a native context. It maps POJOs to their native context (a native pointer) so it can consistently return the same POJO given a pointer value.

    • Method Detail

      • from

        public static <T> T from(com.sun.jna.Pointer pointer)
        Retrieve a POJO that is mapped to a native pointer. This method should be used to easily retrieve a POJO with a native context. This method will only return a POJO if it was previously cached with a call to store(Pointer, Object)
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the POJO to cast.
        Parameters:
        pointer - The pointer of the associated object.
        Returns:
        The cached object.

      • store

        public static void store(com.sun.jna.Pointer pointer,
                         java.lang.Object object)
        Maps a native pointer to a POJO. This method should be used to easily store a POJO with a native context.
        Parameters:
        pointer - The pointer of the associated object.
        object - The object to cache.

      • remove

        public static void remove(com.sun.jna.Pointer pointer)
        Remove a mapped POJO. This method should be used when the native context of the POJO is no longer valid.
        Parameters:
        pointer - The pointer of the associated object.
